{
  "text": "This means that the goals of research design in causal assessment are considerably more complicated than most extant accounts suggest. While there are shared standards [CITATION_1] , as exemplified in Table 1 , there is no single threshold that would allow us to distinguish work that is methodologically adequate (\"science\") from work that is methodologically inadequate (\"nonscience\"). The search for a simple and parsimonious formula (on the order of t-statistics) by which to evaluate methodological goodness is doomed.",
